, a designated section for mums and pups and a physiotherapy room.  Remember seeing the video I shared of Martinez receiving hydrotherapy? This treatment has worked wonders for him.','text'),(393,48,90,'Description_2','It was almost a relief to read the costs for vaccines, medication, rabies shots and then simple things like food, slip leads and puppy/ kitten care packages.  £100 will see 5 dogs and 5 cats medicated for sterilisation and will have change left to buy a 30kg bag of cat and dog food. Seems reasonable? Soi Dog approximately sterilise 2500 animals per month which averages around 15 dogs and 25-40 cats a DAY. Which when you narrow it down, its a huge cost and wouldnt be possible without donations.','text'),(394,48,92,'Description_3','It was almost a relief to read the costs for vaccines, medication, rabies shots and then simple things like food, slip leads and puppy/ kitten care packages.  £100 will see 5 dogs and 5 cats medicated for sterilisation and will have change left to buy a 30kg bag of cat and dog food. Seems reasonable? Soi Dog approximately sterilise 2500 animals per month which averages around 15 dogs and 25-40 cats a DAY. Which when you narrow it down, its a huge cost and wouldnt be possible without donations.','text'),(395,48,94,'Description_4','s a volunteer, our routine hours are 9am-4pm Monday to Friday with a hour for lunch. Our primary duty is to socialise the cats and dogs. This is so that the dogs and cats at the shelter can be adopted into new forever homes. We are each given a designated adult dog run which can consist of 12-25 dogs.  It is essential to teach these dogs to trust people and to teach the dogs to walk on a lead. Almost all of the animals have never been indoors and need to learn to feel comfortable around people. Socialisation is especially important for shy animals and those who have been abused. Many adopters say their new companions are very friendly and comfortable with them, even as soon as they arrive from Thailand – this is because of shelter volunteers.  And its true! During our first week volunteering, some of the dogs wouldnt come near us. Overtime and once enough trust was built, they slowly came further forward until they felt fully comfortable with us. It is a remarkable feeling when you finally have the trust between you and a dog and they want to go on a walk with you. Looking up every few steps for reasurrance that your still there.','text'),(396,48,71,'Upload_Media_File_1','dog1.jpg','file'),(397,48,89,'Upload_Media_File_2','Dog2.jpg','file'),(398,48,91,'Upload_Media_File_3','dog3.jpg','file'),(399,48,93,'Upload_Media_File_4','dog4.jpg','file'),(400,47,168,'LinkedIn_URL','https://www.LinkedIn.com/','url'),(401,47,169,'Twitter_URL','https://www.Twitter.com/','url'),(402,47,170,'MySpace_URL','https://www.MySpace.com/','url'),(403,47,171,'Home_page_URL','https://www.Homepage.com/','url'),(404,47,172,'Facebook_URL','https://www.facebook.com/','url'),(405,47,173,'IMDb_URL','https://www.IMDb.com/','url'),(406,48,96,'LinkedIn_URL','https://www.linkedin.com/uas/login','url'),(407,48,97,'Twitter_URL','https://twitter.com/login','url'),(408,48,100,'Facebook_URL','https://www.facebook.com','url'),(409,48,102,'IMDb_URL','http://www.imdb.com','url'),(410,49,168,'LinkedIn_URL','https://www.LinkedIn.com/','url'),(411,49,169,'Twitter_URL','https://www.Twitter.com/','url'),(412,49,170,'MySpace_URL','https://www.MySpace.com/','url'),(413,49,171,'Home_page_URL','https://www.Homepage.com/','url'),(414,49,172,'Facebook_URL','https://www.facebook.com/','url'),(415,49,173,'IMDb_URL','https://www.IMDb.com/','url'),(416,50,168,'LinkedIn_URL','https://www.LinkedIn.com/','url'),(417,50,169,'Twitter_URL','https://www.Twitter.com/','url'),(418,50,170,'MySpace_URL','https://www.MySpace.com/','url'),(419,50,171,'Home_page_URL','https://www.Homepage.com/','url'),(420,50,172,'Facebook_URL','https://www.facebook.com/','url'),(421,50,173,'IMDb_URL','https://www.IMDb.com/','url'),(422,51,96,'Linked